h 500,000 rows completes processing within the configured timeout without running out of memory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real runtime characteristics (process memory pressure, timeout behavior under load). In-process mocks can hide allocation patterns and scheduler/GC effects. Minimum boundary is OS/process-level execution.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline as a real process against a generated 500k-row CSV and realistic sinks, with production-like timeout settings. Assert completion before timeout and monitor peak RSS/heap to verify it stays below configured memory limits.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the S3 bucket returns a transient 503 error, the pipeline retries with exponential backoff rather than failing the entire batch.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is retry orchestration between pipeline logic and S3 client abstraction. A deterministic fake S3 that returns 503 then success can expose retry/backoff bugs without real AWS calls. Rejected higher level: although behavior mentions \"S3 bucket returns a transient 503,\" the asserted outcome is retry policy control flow (\"retries with exponential backoff\") rather than real network semantics.","test_description":"Wire pipeline + retry policy + S3 client interface with a controllable stub that returns 503 for first N calls then success. Use fake/controlled clock to assert exponential delay schedule and verify batch continues and succeeds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Rows successfully written to PostgreSQL are not duplicated if the pipeline is restarted mid-batch.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Requires durability/idempotency validation across an actual restart boundary plus real DB state continuity. Mocked restarts or purely in-process tests can miss duplicate writes caused by transaction/checkpoint timing during process interruption.","test_description":"Run pipeline process against real PostgreSQL, force interruption mid-batch after a known subset commits, then restart and resume. Assert final table has exactly one copy per logical row (no duplicates) and expected total count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.27,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
